org.jcvi.jillion.maq.bfq

Class BfqFileParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.maq.bfq.BfqFileParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FastqParser

    public abstract class BfqFileParser
extends Object
implements FastqParser
    BfqFileParser is a FastqParser implementation that can read MAQ's binary fastq file format (.bfq files).

    dkatzel

      • create

        public static FastqParser create(File bfqFile)
                          throws IOException
        Create a new FastqParser instance to parse the given binary fastq file (bfq) using the system endian. This is the same as calling: create(bfqFile, ByteOrder.nativeOrder())
        Parameters:
        bfqFile - the binary fastq file to parse.
        Returns:
        a new FastqParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file does not exist.
        NullPointerException - if bfqFile is null.

      • create

        public static FastqParser create(File bfqFile,
                                 ByteOrder endian)
                          throws IOException
        Create a new FastqParser instance to parse the given binary fastq file (bfq) using the given ByteOrder.
        Parameters:
        bfqFile - the binary fastq file to parse.
        endian - the ByteOrder to use to parse the file. Make sure the endian matches the endian of the machine that Maq was run on (or matches the ByteOrder used by the BfqFileWriterBuilder ) that produced the file.
        Returns:
        a new FastqParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem file does not exist.
        NullPointerException - if either parameter is null.

        public boolean canParse()

        Specified by:
